---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="Kilograms to Pounds: Complete Guide with Formula"
  description="Learn how to convert kg to lbs with formulas, mental math tricks, and reference charts. Free guide with instant converter link."
  keywords="kg to lbs, kilograms to pounds, weight conversion, kg to pounds formula, convert kg to lbs, weight converter, metric to imperial weight"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Weight</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Kilograms to Pounds: Complete Guide with Formula" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-05">June 5, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Whether you are checking luggage weight for a flight, tracking your fitness progress, or following a recipe from another country, converting kilograms to pounds is one of the most common unit conversions you will encounter. Here is everything you need to know to do it quickly and accurately.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: The Conversion Formula -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Conversion Formula</h2>
      <p>The exact relationship between kilograms and pounds is straightforward:</p>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">
          1 kg = 2.20462 lbs
        </p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">
          Pounds = Kilograms × 2.20462
        </p>
      </div>
      <p>For most everyday purposes, multiplying by 2.2 gives you a close enough answer. For example, 70 kg × 2.2 = 154 lbs.</p>

      <!-- Section: Quick Mental Math Method -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Quick Mental Math Method</h2>
      <p>When you do not have a calculator handy, use this simple trick:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Double</strong> the kilogram value</li>
        <li><strong>Add 10%</strong> of the doubled number</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> Convert 80 kg to lbs</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>80 × 2 = 160</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>10% of 160 = 16</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>160 + 16 = <strong>176 lbs</strong> (actual: 176.37 lbs)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>This method gets you within 0.2% accuracy every time.</p>

      <!-- Section: Common Conversions Reference -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Conversions Reference</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Kilograms</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Pounds</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">50 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">110.2 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">60 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">132.3 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">70 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">154.3 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">80 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">176.4 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">90 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">198.4 lbs</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">100 kg</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">220.5 lbs</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Pounds to Kilograms -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Going the Other Way: Pounds to Kilograms</h2>
      <p>To convert from pounds to kilograms, divide by 2.20462 or simply multiply by 0.4536:</p>
      <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-mono font-bold text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400">
          Kilograms = Pounds × 0.4536
        </p>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong> 150 lbs × 0.4536 = 68 kg</p>

      <!-- Section: Key Facts -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Key Facts About kg and lbs</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>The kilogram is the SI base unit of mass, used by most countries worldwide</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>The pound (lb) is primarily used in the United States, UK (informally), and a few other nations</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 pound = 16 ounces</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 kilogram = 1000 grams</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>The abbreviation "lb" comes from the Latin word "libra"</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our free weight converter
          </p>
          <a
            href="/convert/weight"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Converter →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
